## Configuration Standards

### **Domain-Driven Configuration**

**Each domain manages its own configuration concerns:**

```text
config/
├── index.js                   # Main configuration loader
├── domains/                   # Domain-specific configuration
│   ├── main.js                # Shared business settings only (minimal)
│   ├── commerce.js            # Self-contained Commerce settings
│   ├── products.js            # Self-contained product settings
│   ├── performance.js         # Self-contained performance settings
│   ├── files.js               # Self-contained file settings
│   ├── runtime.js             # Self-contained runtime settings
│   └── ui.js                  # Self-contained UI settings
```

### **Configuration Patterns**

```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT: Use parameter resolution utilities with standardized names
async function exportProducts(params, config) {
  const { baseUrl, adminUsername, adminPassword } = getCommerceParameters(params, config);
  // Parameters use environment variable format: COMMERCE_BASE_URL, COMMERCE_ADMIN_USERNAME
}

// ✅ CORRECT: Clean object access
async function processData(params, config) {
  const timeout = config.commerce.api.timeout;
  // Use configuration values directly
}

// ✅ CORRECT: Feature receives complete config
async function featureFunction(params, config) {
  // Trust that config contains everything needed
  return await processWithConfig(params, config);
}

// ❌ WRONG: Optional chaining with fallbacks in business logic
const timeout = config.commerce?.api?.timeout || 30000;
```

### **HTTP Headers Pattern**

**When to centralize vs. domain-specific headers based on business and technical constraints:**

```javascript
// ✅ CENTRALIZE: Domain Business Constraints (Commerce - all calls identical)
function buildAuthenticatedRequestOptions(requestOptions, token, config) {
  return {
    headers: {
      ...config.commerce.defaultHeaders,  // Centralized
      ...requestOptions.headers,
      Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
    },
  };
}

// ✅ DOMAIN-SPECIFIC: Technical Constraints (Testing - needs identification)
function buildApiRequestOptions(options) {
  return {
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      'User-Agent': 'Adobe-App-Builder-API-Test',  // Domain-specific
      ...options.headers,
    },
  };
}
```

